# Quartz Blog (articles.kirill-markin.com)

## Structure
- Branch: `v4`
- Content: `content/*.md` (Obsidian-compatible)
- Config: `quartz.config.ts`
- Submodule: `_obsidian/` (only `public/` content is published)
- Note: `content/` links to `_obsidian/public/`

## Commands
```bash
# Initial setup
git submodule update --init --recursive && npm ci

# Dev server
npx quartz build --serve --port 8080

# Production build
npx quartz build
```

## Content
```yaml
---
title: "Title"
date: 2024-02-08
tags: [tag1, tag2]
publish: true  # required
---
```

## Development
- Branch from `v4`: `feat/*` or `fix/*`
- Pull & update submodules before work
- TypeScript with strict types
- NEVER merge locally into protected branches (like `v4`), always use PR workflow:
  1. Create feature branch
  2. Push changes to feature branch
  3. Create PR using `gh pr create`
  4. Merge through GitHub interface or `gh pr merge`

## Deploy
Auto-deploys to gh-pages on merge to `v4` 